{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["43-JHN-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"JHN"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Yuhanna \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The Good News According to Yuhanna \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Yuhanna \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Jhn \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt2","content":["The Good News According to \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Yuhanna \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"JHN 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 1:1"},"In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with Allah, and the Word was Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 1:2"},"The same was in the beginning with Allah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 1:3"},"All things were made through him. Without him, nothing was made that has been made.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 1:4"},"In him was life, and the life was the light of men. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 1:5"},"The light shines in the darkness, and the darkness hasn’t overcome\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word translated “overcome” (κατέλαβεν) can also be translated “comprehended.” It refers to getting a grip\non an enemy to defeat him. "]}],"caller":"+"}," it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 1:6"},"There came a man, sent from Allah, whose name was Yahya. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 1:7"},"The same came as a witness, that he might testify about the light, that all might believe through him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 1:8"},"He was not the light, but was sent that he might testify about the light.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 1:9"},"The true light that enlightens everyone was coming into the world.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 1:10"},"He was in the world, and the world was made through him, and the world didn’t recognise him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 1:11"},"He came to his own, and those who were his own didn’t receive him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 1:12"},"But as many as received him, to them he gave the right to become Allah’s children, to those who believe in his name:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 1:13"},"who were born not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will of man, but of Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 1:14"},"The Word became flesh, and lived amongst us. We saw his glory, such glory as of the one and only Son of the Father, full\nof grace and truth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 1:15"},"Yahya testified about him. He cried out, saying, “This was he of whom I said, ‘He who comes after me has surpassed me,\nfor he was before me.’” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 1:16"},"From his fullness we all received grace upon grace. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 1:17"},"For the law was given through Musa. Grace and truth were realised through Al Masih Isa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 1:18"},"No one has seen Allah at any time. The one and only Son,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU reads “Allah”"]}],"caller":"+"}," who is in the bosom of the Father, has declared him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 1:19"},"This is Yahya’s testimony, when the Jews sent priests and Levites from Jerusalem to ask him, “Who are you?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 1:20"},"He declared, and didn’t deny, but he declared, “I am not the Masih.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 1:21"},"They asked him, “What then? Are you Ilyas?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “I am not.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Are you the prophet?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He answered, “No.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 1:22"},"They said therefore to him, “Who are you? Give us an answer to take back to those who sent us. What do you say about\nyourself?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 1:23"},"He said, “I am the voice of one crying in the wilderness, ‘Make straight the way of the\nLord,’",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 40:3"]}],"caller":"+"}," as Isaiah the prophet said.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 1:24"},"The ones who had been sent were from the Pharisees. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 1:25"},"They asked him, “Why then do you baptise, if you are not the Masih, nor Ilyas, nor the prophet?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 1:26"},"Yahya answered them, “I baptise in water, but amongst you stands one whom you don’t know.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 1:27"},"He is the one who comes after me, who is preferred before me, whose sandal strap I’m not worthy to loosen.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 1:28"},"These things were done in Bethany beyond the Jordan, where Yahya was baptising.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 1:29"},"The next day, he saw Isa coming to him, and said, “Behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:29 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “ἰδοὺ”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an\ninterjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," the Lamb of Allah, who takes away the sin of the world!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 1:30"},"This is he of whom I said, ‘After me comes a man who is preferred before me, for he was before me.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 1:31"},"I didn’t know him, but for this reason I came baptising in water: that he would be revealed to Israel.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 1:32"},"Yahya testified, saying, “I have seen the Spirit descending like a dove out of heaven, and it remained on him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 1:33"},"I didn’t recognise him, but he who sent me to baptise in water said to me, ‘On whomever you will see the Spirit\ndescending and remaining on him is he who baptises in the Holy Spirit.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 1:34"},"I have seen, and have testified that this is the Son of Allah.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 1:35"},"Again, the next day, Yahya was standing with two of his disciples,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 1:36"},"and he looked at Isa as he walked, and said, “Behold, the Lamb of Allah!”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 1:37"},"The two disciples heard him speak, and they followed Isa. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 1:38"},"Isa turned and saw them following, and said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“What are you looking\nfor?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They said to him, “Rabbi” (which is to say, being interpreted, Teacher), “where are you staying?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 1:39"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Come, and see.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They came and saw where he was staying, and they stayed with him that day. It was about the tenth\nhour.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:39 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["4:00 p.m."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 1:40"},"One of the two who heard Yahya and followed him was Andreas, Shima’un Peter’s brother.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JHN 1:41"},"He first found his own brother, Shima’un, and said to him, “We have found the Messiah!” (which is, being interpreted,\nMasih",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:41 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Messiah” (Hebrew) and “Christ” (Greek) both mean “Anointed\nOne”."]}],"caller":"+"},"). \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JHN 1:42"},"He brought him to Isa. Isa looked at him, and said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You are Shima’un the son of Yunus. You shall be called\nCephas”"]}," (which is by interpretation, Peter).",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:42 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Cephas” (Aramaic) and “Peter” (Greek) both mean\n“Rock”."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JHN 1:43"},"On the next day, he was determined to go out into Galilee, and he found Philip. Isa said to him,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Follow me.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JHN 1:44"},"Now Philip was from Bethsaida, of the city of Andreas and Peter.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"JHN 1:45"},"Philip found Nathanael, and said to him, “We have found him, of whom Musa in the law, and the prophets, wrote: Isa of\nNazareth, the son of Yusuf.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"JHN 1:46"},"Nathanael said to him, “Can any good thing come out of Nazareth?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Philip said to him, “Come and see.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"JHN 1:47"},"Isa saw Nathanael coming to him, and said about him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Behold, an Israelite indeed, in whom is no\ndeceit!”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"JHN 1:48"},"Nathanael said to him, “How do you know me?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Before Philip called you, when you were under the fig tree, I saw\nyou.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"JHN 1:49"},"Nathanael answered him, “Rabbi, you are the Son of Allah! You are King of Israel!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"JHN 1:50"},"Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Because I told you, ‘I saw you underneath the fig tree,’ do you believe? You will see greater\nthings than these!”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"JHN 1:51"},"He said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly, I tell you all, hereafter you will see heaven opened, and the angels of Allah\nascending and descending on the Son of Man.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"JHN 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 2:1"},"The third day, there was a wedding in Cana of Galilee. Isa’s mother was there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 2:2"},"Isa also was invited, with his disciples, to the wedding. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 2:3"},"When the wine ran out, Isa’s mother said to him, “They have no wine.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 2:4"},"Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Woman, what does that have to do with you and me? My hour has not yet\ncome.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 2:5"},"His mother said to the servants, “Whatever he says to you, do it.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 2:6"},"Now there were six water pots of stone set there after the Jews’ way of purifying, containing two or three\nmetretes",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["2 to 3 metretes is about 20 to 30 U. S. Gallons, or 75 to 115\nlitres."]}],"caller":"+"}," apiece. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 2:7"},"Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Fill the water pots with water.”"]}," So they filled them up to the brim.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 2:8"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Now draw some out, and take it to the ruler of the\nfeast.”"]}," So they took it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 2:9"},"When the ruler of the feast tasted the water now become wine, and didn’t know where it came from (but the servants who had\ndrawn the water knew), the ruler of the feast called the bridegroom\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 2:10"},"and said to him, “Everyone serves the good wine first, and when the guests have drunk freely, then that which is worse.\nYou have kept the good wine until now!” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 2:11"},"This beginning of his signs Isa did in Cana of Galilee, and revealed his glory; and his disciples believed in him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 2:12"},"After this, he went down to Capernaum, he, and his mother, his brothers, and his disciples; and they stayed there a few\ndays. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 2:13"},"The Passover of the Jews was at hand, and Isa went up to Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 2:14"},"He found in the temple those who sold oxen, sheep, and doves, and the changers of money sitting.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 2:15"},"He made a whip of cords, and threw all out of the temple, both the sheep and the oxen; and he poured out the changers’\nmoney and overthrew their tables. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 2:16"},"To those who sold the doves, he said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Take these things out of here! Don’t make my Father’s house a\nmarketplace!”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 2:17"},"His disciples remembered that it was written, “Zeal for your house will eat me\nup.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["2:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 69:9"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 2:18"},"The Jews therefore answered him, “What sign do you show us, seeing that you do these things?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 2:19"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it\nup.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 2:20"},"The Jews therefore said, “It took forty-six years to build this temple! Will you raise it up in three days?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 2:21"},"But he spoke of the temple of his body. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 2:22"},"When therefore he was raised from the dead, his disciples remembered that he said this, and they believed the Scripture,\nand the word which Isa had said. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 2:23"},"Now when he was in Jerusalem at the Passover, during the feast, many believed in his name, observing his signs which he\ndid. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 2:24"},"But Isa didn’t entrust himself to them, because he knew everyone,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 2:25"},"and because he didn’t need for anyone to testify concerning man; for he himself knew what was in man.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"JHN 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 3:1"},"Now there was a man of the Pharisees named Nicodemus, a ruler of the Jews.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 3:2"},"The same came to him by night, and said to him, “Rabbi, we know that you are a teacher come from Allah, for no one can do\nthese signs that you do, unless Allah is with him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 3:3"},"Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly, I tell you, unless one is born anew,\n"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word translated “anew” here and in Yuhanna\n3:7 (ἄνωθεν) also means “again” and “from above”."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["he can’t see Allah’s\nKingdom.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 3:4"},"Nicodemus said to him, “How can a man be born when he is old? Can he enter a second time into his mother’s womb, and be\nborn?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 3:5"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly I tell you, unless one is born of water and spirit, he can’t enter into Allah’s\nKingdom."]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 3:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["That which is born of the flesh is flesh. That which is born of the Spirit is spirit.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 3:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t marvel that I said to you, ‘You must be born anew.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 3:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The wind"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The same Greek word (πνεῦμα) means wind, breath, and\nspirit."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["blows where it wants to, and you hear its sound, but don’t know where it comes from and where it is going. So is\neveryone who is born of the Spirit.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 3:9"},"Nicodemus answered him, “How can these things be?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 3:10"},"Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Are you the teacher of Israel, and don’t understand these things?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 3:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly I tell you, we speak that which we know, and testify of that which we have seen, and you don’t\nreceive our witness. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 3:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If I told you earthly things and you don’t believe, how will you believe if I tell you heavenly things?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 3:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["No one has ascended into heaven but he who descended out of heaven, the Son of Man, who is in heaven.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 3:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["As Musa lifted up the serpent in the wilderness, even so must the Son of Man be lifted up,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 3:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["that whoever believes in him should not perish, but have eternal life.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 3:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For Allah so loved the world, that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish, but\nhave eternal life. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 3:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For Allah didn’t send his Son into the world to judge the world, but that the world should be saved through him.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 3:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who believes in him is not judged. He who doesn’t believe has been judged already, because he has not believed in\nthe name of the one and only Son of Allah. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 3:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["This is the judgement, that the light has come into the world, and men loved the darkness rather than the light; for\ntheir works were evil. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 3:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For everyone who does evil hates the light, and doesn’t come to the light, lest his works would be exposed.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 3:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But he who does the truth comes to the light, that his works may be revealed, that they have been done in\nAllah.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 3:22"},"After these things, Isa came with his disciples into the land of Judea. He stayed there with them and baptised.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 3:23"},"Yahya also was baptising in Enon near Salim, because there was much water there. They came, and were baptised;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 3:24"},"for Yahya was not yet thrown into prison. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 3:25"},"Therefore a dispute arose on the part of Yahya’s disciples with some Jews about purification.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 3:26"},"They came to Yahya and said to him, “Rabbi, he who was with you beyond the Jordan, to whom you have testified, behold, he\nbaptises, and everyone is coming to him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 3:27"},"Yahya answered, “A man can receive nothing unless it has been given him from heaven.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 3:28"},"You yourselves testify that I said, ‘I am not the Masih,’ but, ‘I have been sent before him.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 3:29"},"He who has the bride is the bridegroom; but the friend of the bridegroom, who stands and hears him, rejoices greatly\nbecause of the bridegroom’s voice. This, my joy, therefore is made full.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 3:30"},"He must increase, but I must decrease. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 3:31"},"He who comes from above is above all. He who is from the earth belongs to the earth and speaks of the earth. He who comes\nfrom heaven is above all. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 3:32"},"What he has seen and heard, of that he testifies; and no one receives his witness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 3:33"},"He who has received his witness has set his seal to this, that Allah is true.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 3:34"},"For he whom Allah has sent speaks the words of Allah; for Allah gives the Spirit without measure.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 3:35"},"The Father loves the Son, and has given all things into his hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 3:36"},"One who believes in the Son has eternal life, but one who disobeys\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:36 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The same word can be translated “disobeys” or “disbelieves” in this\ncontext."]}],"caller":"+"}," the Son won’t see life, but the wrath of Allah remains on him.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"JHN 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 4:1"},"Therefore when the Lord knew that the Pharisees had heard that Isa was making and baptising more disciples than Yahya\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 4:2"},"(although Isa himself didn’t baptise, but his disciples), \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 4:3"},"he left Judea and departed into Galilee. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 4:4"},"He needed to pass through Samaria. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 4:5"},"So he came to a city of Samaria, called Sychar, near the parcel of ground that Yaqub gave to his son, Yusuf.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 4:6"},"Yaqub’s well was there. Isa therefore, being tired from his journey, sat down by the well. It was about the sixth\nhour.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["noon"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 4:7"},"A woman of Samaria came to draw water. Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Give me a\ndrink.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 4:8"},"For his disciples had gone away into the city to buy food. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 4:9"},"The Samaritan woman therefore said to him, “How is it that you, being a Jew, ask for a drink from me, a Samaritan woman?”\n(For Jews have no dealings with Samaritans.) \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 4:10"},"Isa answered her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If you knew the gift of Allah, and who it is who says to you, ‘Give me a drink,’ you would have\nasked him, and he would have given you living water.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 4:11"},"The woman said to him, “Sir, you have nothing to draw with, and the well is deep. So where do you get that living water?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 4:12"},"Are you greater than our father, Yaqub, who gave us the well and drank from it himself, as did his children and his\nlivestock?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 4:13"},"Isa answered her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Everyone who drinks of this water will thirst again,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 4:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["but whoever drinks of the water that I will give him will never thirst again; but the water that I will give him\nwill become in him a well of water springing up to eternal life.”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 4:15"},"The woman said to him, “Sir, give me this water, so that I don’t get thirsty, neither come all the way here to draw.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 4:16"},"Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Go, call your husband, and come here.”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 4:17"},"The woman answered, “I have no husband.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You said well, ‘I have no husband,’ "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 4:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for you have had five husbands; and he whom you now have is not your husband. This you have said\ntruly.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 4:19"},"The woman said to him, “Sir, I perceive that you are a prophet.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 4:20"},"Our fathers worshipped in this mountain, and you Jews say that in Jerusalem is the place where people ought to worship.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 4:21"},"Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Woman, believe me, the hour comes, when neither in this mountain, nor in Jerusalem, will you\nworship the Father. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 4:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You worship that which you don’t know. We worship that which we know; for salvation is from the Jews.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 4:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But the hour comes, and now is, when the true worshippers will worship the Father in spirit and truth, for the\nFather seeks such to be his worshippers. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 4:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Allah is spirit, and those who worship him must worship in spirit and\ntruth.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 4:25"},"The woman said to him, “I know that Messiah comes, he who is called Masih. When he has come, he will declare to us all\nthings.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 4:26"},"Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am he, the one who speaks to you.”"]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 4:27"},"At this, his disciples came. They marvelled that he was speaking with a woman; yet no one said, “What are you looking\nfor?” or, “Why do you speak with her?” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 4:28"},"So the woman left her water pot, went away into the city, and said to the people,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 4:29"},"“Come, see a man who told me everything that I did. Can this be the Masih?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 4:30"},"They went out of the city, and were coming to him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 4:31"},"In the meanwhile, the disciples urged him, saying, “Rabbi, eat.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 4:32"},"But he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I have food to eat that you don’t know\nabout.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 4:33"},"The disciples therefore said to one another, “Has anyone brought him something to eat?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 4:34"},"Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“My food is to do the will of him who sent me and to accomplish his work.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 4:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t you say, ‘There are yet four months until the harvest?’ Behold, I tell you, lift up your eyes and look at the\nfields, that they are white for harvest already. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 4:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who reaps receives wages and gathers fruit to eternal life; that both he who sows and he who reaps may rejoice\ntogether. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 4:37"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For in this the saying is true, ‘One sows, and another reaps.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 4:38"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I sent you to reap that for which you haven’t laboured. Others have laboured, and you have entered into their\nlabour.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 4:39"},"From that city many of the Samaritans believed in him because of the word of the woman, who testified, “He told me\neverything that I did.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 4:40"},"So when the Samaritans came to him, they begged him to stay with them. He stayed there two days.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JHN 4:41"},"Many more believed because of his word. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JHN 4:42"},"They said to the woman, “Now we believe, not because of your speaking; for we have heard for ourselves, and know that\nthis is indeed the Masih, the Saviour of the world.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JHN 4:43"},"After the two days he went out from there and went into Galilee.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JHN 4:44"},"For Isa himself testified that a prophet has no honour in his own country.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"JHN 4:45"},"So when he came into Galilee, the Galileans received him, having seen all the things that he did in Jerusalem at the\nfeast, for they also went to the feast. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"JHN 4:46"},"Isa came therefore again to Cana of Galilee, where he made the water into wine. There was a certain nobleman whose son\nwas sick at Capernaum. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"JHN 4:47"},"When he heard that Isa had come out of Judea into Galilee, he went to him, and begged him that he would come down and\nheal his son, for he was at the point of death. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"JHN 4:48"},"Isa therefore said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Unless you see signs and wonders, you will in no way\nbelieve.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"JHN 4:49"},"The nobleman said to him, “Sir, come down before my child dies.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"JHN 4:50"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Go your way. Your son lives.”"]}," The man believed the word that Isa spoke to him, and he went his\nway. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"JHN 4:51"},"As he was now going down, his servants met him and reported, saying “Your child lives!”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"JHN 4:52"},"So he enquired of them the hour when he began to get better. They said therefore to him, “Yesterday at the seventh\nhour,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:52 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1:00 p.m."]}],"caller":"+"}," the fever left him.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"JHN 4:53"},"So the father knew that it was at that hour in which Isa said to him,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Your son lives.”"]}," He believed, as did his whole house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"JHN 4:54"},"This is again the second sign that Isa did, having come out of Judea into Galilee.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"JHN 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 5:1"},"After these things, there was a feast of the Jews, and Isa went up to Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 5:2"},"Now in Jerusalem by the sheep gate, there is a pool, which is called in Hebrew, “Bethesda”, having five porches.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 5:3"},"In these lay a great multitude of those who were sick, blind, lame, or paralysed, waiting for the moving of the water;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 5:4"},"for an angel went down at certain times into the pool and stirred up the water. Whoever stepped in first after the\nstirring of the water was healed of whatever disease he had.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU omits from “waiting” in verse 3 to the end of verse\n4."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 5:5"},"A certain man was there who had been sick for thirty-eight years.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 5:6"},"When Isa saw him lying there, and knew that he had been sick for a long time, he asked him,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Do you want to be made well?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 5:7"},"The sick man answered him, “Sir, I have no one to put me into the pool when the water is stirred up, but while I’m coming,\nanother steps down before me.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 5:8"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Arise, take up your mat, and walk.”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 5:9"},"Immediately, the man was made well, and took up his mat and walked.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Now it was the Sabbath on that day. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 5:10"},"So the Jews said to him who was cured, “It is the Sabbath. It is not lawful for you to carry the mat.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 5:11"},"He answered them, “He who made me well said to me, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘Take up your mat and\nwalk.’"]},"” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 5:12"},"Then they asked him, “Who is the man who said to you, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘Take up your mat and\nwalk’"]},"?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 5:13"},"But he who was healed didn’t know who it was, for Isa had withdrawn, a crowd being in the place.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 5:14"},"Afterward Isa found him in the temple, and said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Behold, you are made well. Sin no more, so that nothing\nworse happens to you.” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 5:15"},"The man went away, and told the Jews that it was Isa who had made him well.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 5:16"},"For this cause the Jews persecuted Isa, and sought to kill him, because he did these things on the Sabbath.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 5:17"},"But Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“My Father is still working, so I am working,\ntoo.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 5:18"},"For this cause therefore the Jews sought all the more to kill him, because he not only broke the Sabbath, but also called\nAllah his own Father, making himself equal with Allah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 5:19"},"Isa therefore answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly, I tell you, the Son can do nothing of himself, but what he sees the\nFather doing. For whatever things he does, these the Son also does likewise.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 5:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For the Father has affection for the Son, and shows him all things that he himself does. He will show him greater\nworks than these, that you may marvel. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 5:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For as the Father raises the dead and gives them life, even so the Son also gives life to whom he desires.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 5:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For the Father judges no one, but he has given all judgement to the Son,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 5:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["that all may honour the Son, even as they honour the Father. He who doesn’t honour the Son doesn’t honour the Father\nwho sent him."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 5:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly I tell you, he who hears my word and believes him who sent me has eternal life, and doesn’t come\ninto judgement, but has passed out of death into life. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 5:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly I tell you, the hour comes, and now is, when the dead will hear the Son of Allah’s voice; and those\nwho hear will live. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 5:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For as the Father has life in himself, even so he gave to the Son also to have life in himself.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 5:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He also gave him authority to execute judgement, because he is a son of man.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 5:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t marvel at this, for the hour comes in which all who are in the tombs will hear his voice,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 5:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and will come out; those who have done good, to the resurrection of life; and those who have done evil, to the\nresurrection of judgement. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 5:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I can of myself do nothing. As I hear, I judge, and my judgement is righteous; because I don’t seek my own will, but\nthe will of my Father who sent me."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 5:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If I testify about myself, my witness is not valid. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 5:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["It is another who testifies about me. I know that the testimony which he testifies about me is true.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 5:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You have sent to Yahya, and he has testified to the truth.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 5:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But the testimony which I receive is not from man. However, I say these things that you may be saved.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 5:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He was the burning and shining lamp, and you were willing to rejoice for a while in his light.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 5:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But the testimony which I have is greater than that of Yahya, for the works which the Father gave me to accomplish,\nthe very works that I do, testify about me, that the Father has sent me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 5:37"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The Father himself, who sent me, has testified about me. You have neither heard his voice at any time, nor seen his\nform. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 5:38"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You don’t have his word living in you; because you don’t believe him whom he\nsent."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 5:39"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You search the Scriptures, because you think that in them you have eternal life; and these are they which testify\nabout me. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 5:40"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Yet you will not come to me, that you may have life. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JHN 5:41"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I don’t receive glory from men. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JHN 5:42"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But I know you, that you don’t have Allah’s love in yourselves.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JHN 5:43"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I have come in my Father’s name, and you don’t receive me. If another comes in his own name, you will receive him.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JHN 5:44"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["How can you believe, who receive glory from one another, and you don’t seek the glory that comes from the only\nAllah?"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"JHN 5:45"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Don’t think that I will accuse you to the Father. There is one who accuses you, even Musa, on whom you have set\nyour hope. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"JHN 5:46"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For if you believed Musa, you would believe me; for he wrote about me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"JHN 5:47"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But if you don’t believe his writings, how will you believe my\nwords?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"JHN 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 6:1"},"After these things, Isa went away to the other side of the sea of Galilee, which is also called the Sea of Tiberias.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 6:2"},"A great multitude followed him, because they saw his signs which he did on those who were sick.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 6:3"},"Isa went up into the mountain, and he sat there with his disciples.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 6:4"},"Now the Passover, the feast of the Jews, was at hand. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 6:5"},"Isa therefore lifting up his eyes, and seeing that a great multitude was coming to him, said to Philip,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Where are we to buy bread, that these may eat?”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 6:6"},"He said this to test him, for he himself knew what he would do.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 6:7"},"Philip answered him, “Two hundred denarii",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A denarius was a silver coin worth about a day’s wages for an\nagricultural labourer, so 200 denarii would be between 6 and 7 month’s\npay."]}],"caller":"+"}," worth of bread is not sufficient for them, that every one of them may receive a little.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 6:8"},"One of his disciples, Andreas, Shima’un Peter’s brother, said to him,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 6:9"},"“There is a boy here who has five barley loaves and two fish, but what are these amongst so many?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 6:10"},"Isa said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Have the people sit down.”"]}," Now there was much grass in that place. So the men sat down, in number\nabout five thousand. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 6:11"},"Isa took the loaves; and having given thanks, he distributed to the disciples, and the disciples to those who were\nsitting down; likewise also of the fish as much as they desired.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 6:12"},"When they were filled, he said to his disciples, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Gather up the broken pieces which are left over, that nothing be\nlost.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 6:13"},"So they gathered them up, and filled twelve baskets with broken pieces from the five barley loaves, which were left over\nby those who had eaten. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 6:14"},"When therefore the people saw the sign which Isa did, they said, “This is truly the prophet who comes into the world.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 6:15"},"Isa therefore, perceiving that they were about to come and take him by force to make him king, withdrew again to the\nmountain by himself. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 6:16"},"When evening came, his disciples went down to the sea. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 6:17"},"They entered into the boat, and were going over the sea to Capernaum. It was now dark, and Isa had not come to them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 6:18"},"The sea was tossed by a great wind blowing. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 6:19"},"When therefore they had rowed about twenty-five or thirty stadia,\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["25 to 30 stadia is about 5 to 6 kilometres or about 3 to 4\nmiles"]}],"caller":"+"}," they saw Isa walking on the sea,",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["6:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["See Ayyub\n9:8"]}],"caller":"+"}," and drawing near to the boat; and they were afraid. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 6:20"},"But he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“It is I."]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, I\nAM"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t be afraid.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 6:21"},"They were willing therefore to receive him into the boat. Immediately the boat was at the land where they were going.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 6:22"},"On the next day, the multitude that stood on the other side of the sea saw that there was no other boat there, except the\none in which his disciples had embarked, and that Isa hadn’t entered with his disciples into the boat, but his disciples had\ngone away alone. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 6:23"},"However boats from Tiberias came near to the place where they ate the bread after the Lord had given thanks.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 6:24"},"When the multitude therefore saw that Isa wasn’t there, nor his disciples, they themselves got into the boats, and came\nto Capernaum, seeking Isa. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 6:25"},"When they found him on the other side of the sea, they asked him, “Rabbi, when did you come here?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 6:26"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly I tell you, you seek me, not because you saw signs, but because you ate of the\nloaves, and were filled. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 6:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t work for the food which perishes, but for the food which remains to eternal life, which the Son of Man will\ngive to you. For Allah the Father has sealed him.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 6:28"},"They said therefore to him, “What must we do, that we may work the works of Allah?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 6:29"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“This is the work of Allah, that you believe in him whom he has\nsent.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 6:30"},"They said therefore to him, “What then do you do for a sign, that we may see and believe you? What work do you do?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 6:31"},"Our fathers ate the manna in the wilderness. As it is written, ‘He gave them bread out of\nheaven",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek and Hebrew use the same word for “heaven”, “the heavens”, “the sky”, and “the\nair”."]}],"caller":"+"}," to eat.’”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["6:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 16:4; Nehemiah 9:15;\nZabur 78:24-25"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 6:32"},"Isa therefore said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly, I tell you, it wasn’t Musa who gave you the bread out of heaven, but my\nFather gives you the true bread out of heaven. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 6:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For the bread of Allah is that which comes down out of heaven, and gives life to the\nworld.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 6:34"},"They said therefore to him, “Lord, always give us this bread.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 6:35"},"Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am the bread of life. Whoever comes to me will not be hungry, and whoever believes in me will\nnever be thirsty. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 6:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But I told you that you have seen me, and yet you don’t believe.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 6:37"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["All those whom the Father gives me will come to me. He who comes to me I will in no way throw out.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 6:38"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For I have come down from heaven, not to do my own will, but the will of him who sent me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 6:39"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["This is the will of my Father who sent me, that of all he has given to me I should lose nothing, but should raise\nhim up at the last day. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 6:40"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["This is the will of the one who sent me, that everyone who sees the Son, and believes in him, should have eternal\nlife; and I will raise him up at the last day.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JHN 6:41"},"The Jews therefore murmured concerning him, because he said,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am the bread which came down out of heaven.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JHN 6:42"},"They said, “Isn’t this Isa, the son of Yusuf, whose father and mother we know? How then does he say,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘I have come down out of heaven?’” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JHN 6:43"},"Therefore Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Don’t murmur amongst yourselves.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JHN 6:44"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["No one can come to me unless the Father who sent me draws him, and I will raise him up in the last day.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"JHN 6:45"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["It is written in the prophets, ‘They will all be taught by Allah.’\n"]}," ",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["6:45 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 54:13"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Therefore everyone who hears from the Father and has learnt, comes to me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"JHN 6:46"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Not that anyone has seen the Father, except he who is from Allah. He has seen the Father.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"JHN 6:47"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly, I tell you, he who believes in me has eternal life.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"JHN 6:48"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am the bread of life. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"JHN 6:49"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Your fathers ate the manna in the wilderness and they died.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"JHN 6:50"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["This is the bread which comes down out of heaven, that anyone may eat of it and not die.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"JHN 6:51"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am the living bread which came down out of heaven. If anyone eats of this bread, he will live forever. Yes, the\nbread which I will give for the life of the world is my flesh.”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"JHN 6:52"},"The Jews therefore contended with one another, saying, “How can this man give us his flesh to eat?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"JHN 6:53"},"Isa therefore said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly I tell you, unless you eat the flesh of the Son of Man and drink his\nblood, you don’t have life in yourselves. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"JHN 6:54"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who eats my flesh and drinks my blood has eternal life, and I will raise him up at the last day.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"JHN 6:55"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For my flesh is food indeed, and my blood is drink indeed.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"JHN 6:56"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who eats my flesh and drinks my blood lives in me, and I in him.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57","sid":"JHN 6:57"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["As the living Father sent me, and I live because of the Father; so he who feeds on me, he will also live because of\nme. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58","sid":"JHN 6:58"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["This is the bread which came down out of heaven—not as our fathers ate the manna, and died. He who eats this bread\nwill live forever.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59","sid":"JHN 6:59"},"He said these things in the synagogue, as he taught in Capernaum.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60","sid":"JHN 6:60"},"Therefore many of his disciples, when they heard this, said, “This is a hard saying! Who can listen to it?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61","sid":"JHN 6:61"},"But Isa knowing in himself that his disciples murmured at this, said to them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Does this cause you to stumble? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62","sid":"JHN 6:62"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Then what if you would see the Son of Man ascending to where he was before?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63","sid":"JHN 6:63"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["It is the spirit who gives life. The flesh profits nothing. The words that I speak to you are spirit, and are life.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"64","sid":"JHN 6:64"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But there are some of you who don’t believe.”"]}," For Isa knew from the beginning who they were who didn’t believe,\nand who it was who would betray him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"65","sid":"JHN 6:65"},"He said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“For this cause I have said to you that no one can come to me, unless it is given to him by my\nFather.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"66","sid":"JHN 6:66"},"At this, many of his disciples went back, and walked no more with him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"67","sid":"JHN 6:67"},"Isa said therefore to the twelve, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You don’t also want to go away, do\nyou?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"68","sid":"JHN 6:68"},"Shima’un Peter answered him, “Lord, to whom would we go? You have the words of eternal life.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"69","sid":"JHN 6:69"},"We have come to believe and know that you are the Masih, the Son of the living Allah.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"70","sid":"JHN 6:70"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Didn’t I choose you, the twelve, and one of you is a\nShaitan?”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"71","sid":"JHN 6:71"},"Now he spoke of Yehuda, the son of Shima’un Iscariot, for it was he who would betray him, being one of the twelve.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7","sid":"JHN 7"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 7:1"},"After these things, Isa was walking in Galilee, for he wouldn’t walk in Judea, because the Jews sought to kill him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 7:2"},"Now the feast of the Jews, the Feast of Booths, was at hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 7:3"},"His brothers therefore said to him, “Depart from here and go into Judea, that your disciples also may see your works which\nyou do. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 7:4"},"For no one does anything in secret while he seeks to be known openly. If you do these things, reveal yourself to the\nworld.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 7:5"},"For even his brothers didn’t believe in him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 7:6"},"Isa therefore said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“My time has not yet come, but your time is always ready.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 7:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The world can’t hate you, but it hates me, because I testify about it, that its works are evil.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 7:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You go up to the feast. I am not yet going up to this feast, because my time is not yet\nfulfilled.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 7:9"},"Having said these things to them, he stayed in Galilee. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 7:10"},"But when his brothers had gone up to the feast, then he also went up, not publicly, but as it were in secret.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 7:11"},"The Jews therefore sought him at the feast, and said, “Where is he?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 7:12"},"There was much murmuring amongst the multitudes concerning him. Some said, “He is a good man.” Others said, “Not so, but\nhe leads the multitude astray.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 7:13"},"Yet no one spoke openly of him for fear of the Jews. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 7:14"},"But when it was now the middle of the feast, Isa went up into the temple and taught.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 7:15"},"The Jews therefore marvelled, saying, “How does this man know letters, having never been educated?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 7:16"},"Isa therefore answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“My teaching is not mine, but his who sent me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 7:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If anyone desires to do his will, he will know about the teaching, whether it is from Allah, or if I am speaking\nfrom myself. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 7:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who speaks from himself seeks his own glory, but he who seeks the glory of him who sent him is true, and no\nunrighteousness is in him. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 7:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Didn’t Musa give you the law, and yet none of you keeps the law? Why do you seek to kill\nme?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 7:20"},"The multitude answered, “You have a demon! Who seeks to kill you?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 7:21"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I did one work and you all marvel because of it.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 7:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Musa has given you circumcision (not that it is of Musa, but of the fathers), and on the Sabbath you circumcise a\nboy. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 7:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If a boy receives circumcision on the Sabbath, that the law of Musa may not be broken, are you angry with me,\nbecause I made a man completely healthy on the Sabbath? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 7:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t judge according to appearance, but judge righteous judgement.”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 7:25"},"Therefore some of them of Jerusalem said, “Isn’t this he whom they seek to kill?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 7:26"},"Behold, he speaks openly, and they say nothing to him. Can it be that the rulers indeed know that this is truly the\nMasih? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 7:27"},"However we know where this man comes from, but when the Masih comes, no one will know where he comes from.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 7:28"},"Isa therefore cried out in the temple, teaching and saying,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You both know me, and know where I am from. I have not come of myself, but he who sent me is true, whom you don’t know.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 7:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I know him, because I am from him, and he sent me.”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 7:30"},"They sought therefore to take him; but no one laid a hand on him, because his hour had not yet come.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 7:31"},"But of the multitude, many believed in him. They said, “When the Masih comes, he won’t do more signs than those which\nthis man has done, will he?” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 7:32"},"The Pharisees heard the multitude murmuring these things concerning him, and the chief priests and the Pharisees sent\nofficers to arrest him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 7:33"},"Then Isa said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I will be with you a little while longer, then I go to him who sent me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 7:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You will seek me, and won’t find me. You can’t come where I\nam.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 7:35"},"The Jews therefore said amongst themselves, “Where will this man go that we won’t find him? Will he go to the Dispersion\namongst the Greeks, and teach the Greeks? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 7:36"},"What is this word that he said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘You will seek me, and won’t find\nme;’"]}," and ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘Where I am, you can’t come’"]},"?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 7:37"},"Now on the last and greatest day of the feast, Isa stood and cried out,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If anyone is thirsty, let him come to me and drink! "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 7:38"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who believes in me, as the Scripture has said, from within him will flow rivers of living\nwater.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 7:39"},"But he said this about the Spirit, which those believing in him were to receive. For the Holy Spirit was not yet given,\nbecause Isa wasn’t yet glorified. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 7:40"},"Many of the multitude therefore, when they heard these words, said, “This is truly the prophet.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JHN 7:41"},"Others said, “This is the Masih.” But some said, “What, does the Masih come out of Galilee?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JHN 7:42"},"Hasn’t the Scripture said that the Masih comes of the offspring",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:42 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, seed"]}],"caller":"+"}," of Dawood, ",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["7:42 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Samuel 7:12"]}],"caller":"+"}," and from\nBethlehem,",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["7:42 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Micah 5:2"]}],"caller":"+"}," the village where Dawood was?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JHN 7:43"},"So a division arose in the multitude because of him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JHN 7:44"},"Some of them would have arrested him, but no one laid hands on him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"JHN 7:45"},"The officers therefore came to the chief priests and Pharisees, and they said to them, “Why didn’t you bring him?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"JHN 7:46"},"The officers answered, “No man ever spoke like this man!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"JHN 7:47"},"The Pharisees therefore answered them, “You aren’t also led astray, are you?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"JHN 7:48"},"Have any of the rulers believed in him, or of the Pharisees?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"JHN 7:49"},"But this multitude that doesn’t know the law is cursed.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"JHN 7:50"},"Nicodemus (he who came to him by night, being one of them) said to them,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"JHN 7:51"},"“Does our law judge a man, unless it first hears from him personally and knows what he does?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"JHN 7:52"},"They answered him, “Are you also from Galilee? Search, and see that no prophet has arisen out of\nGalilee.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["7:52 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["See Isaiah 9:1; Matti 4:13-16"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"JHN 7:53"},"Everyone went to his own house, \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8","sid":"JHN 8"},{"type":"para","marker":"nb","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 8:1"},"but Isa went to the Mount of Olives. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 8:2"},"Now very early in the morning, he came again into the temple, and all the people came to him. He sat down and taught them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 8:3"},"The scribes and the Pharisees brought a woman taken in adultery. Having set her in the middle,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 8:4"},"they told him, “Teacher, we found this woman in adultery, in the very act.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 8:5"},"Now in our law, Musa commanded us to stone such women.",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["8:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Leviticus 20:10; Deuteronomy 22:22"]}],"caller":"+"}," What then do you say about her?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 8:6"},"They said this testing him, that they might have something to accuse him of.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But Isa stooped down and wrote on the ground with his finger.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 8:7"},"But when they continued asking him, he looked up and said to them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He who is without sin amongst you, let him throw the first stone at her.”\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 8:8"},"Again he stooped down and wrote on the ground with his finger.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 8:9"},"They, when they heard it, being convicted by their conscience, went out one by one, beginning from the oldest, even to the\nlast. Isa was left alone with the woman where she was, in the middle.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 8:10"},"Isa, standing up, saw her and said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Woman, where are your accusers? Did no one condemn\nyou?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 8:11"},"She said, “No one, Lord.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Neither do I condemn you. Go your way. From now on, sin no\nmore.”"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU includes Yuhanna 7:53–Yuhanna 8:11, but puts brackets around it to indicate that the textual\ncritics had less confidence that this was original."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 8:12"},"Again, therefore, Isa spoke to them, saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am the light of the\nworld."]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["8:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 60:1"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who follows me will not walk in the darkness, but will have the light of\nlife.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 8:13"},"The Pharisees therefore said to him, “You testify about yourself. Your testimony is not valid.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 8:14"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Even if I testify about myself, my testimony is true, for I know where I came from, and where I\nam going; but you don’t know where I came from, or where I am going.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 8:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You judge according to the flesh. I judge no one. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 8:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Even if I do judge, my judgement is true, for I am not alone, but I am with the Father who sent me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 8:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["It’s also written in your law that the testimony of two people is\nvalid."]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["8:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 17:6; 19:15"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 8:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am one who testifies about myself, and the Father who sent me testifies about\nme.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 8:19"},"They said therefore to him, “Where is your Father?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You know neither me nor my Father. If you knew me, you would know my Father\nalso.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 8:20"},"Isa spoke these words in the treasury, as he taught in the temple. Yet no one arrested him, because his hour had not yet\ncome. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 8:21"},"Isa said therefore again to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am going away, and you will seek me, and you will die in your sins. Where I go,\nyou can’t come.” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 8:22"},"The Jews therefore said, “Will he kill himself, because he says,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘Where I am going, you can’t come’"]},"?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 8:23"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You are from beneath. I am from above. You are of this world. I am not of this world.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 8:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I said therefore to you that you will die in your sins; for unless you believe that I\nam"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, I AM"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["he, you will die in your sins.”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 8:25"},"They said therefore to him, “Who are you?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Just what I have been saying to you from the beginning.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 8:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I have many things to speak and to judge concerning you. However he who sent me is true; and the things which I\nheard from him, these I say to the world.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 8:27"},"They didn’t understand that he spoke to them about the Father.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 8:28"},"Isa therefore said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“When you have lifted up the Son of Man, then you will know that I am he, and I do\nnothing of myself, but as my Father taught me, I say these things.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 8:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who sent me is with me. The Father hasn’t left me alone, for I always do the things that are pleasing to\nhim.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 8:30"},"As he spoke these things, many believed in him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 8:31"},"Isa therefore said to those Jews who had believed him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If you remain in my word, then you are truly my disciples.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 8:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You will know the truth, and the truth will make you free.”\n"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["8:32 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 119:45"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 8:33"},"They answered him, “We are Ibrahim’s offspring, and have never been in bondage to anyone. How do you say,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘You will be made free’"]},"?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 8:34"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly I tell you, everyone who commits sin is the bondservant of sin.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 8:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["A bondservant doesn’t live in the house forever. A son remains forever.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 8:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If therefore the Son makes you free, you will be free indeed.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 8:37"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I know that you are Ibrahim’s offspring, yet you seek to kill me, because my word finds no place in you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 8:38"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I say the things which I have seen with my Father; and you also do the things which you have seen with your\nfather.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 8:39"},"They answered him, “Our father is Ibrahim.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If you were Ibrahim’s children, you would do the works of Ibrahim.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 8:40"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But now you seek to kill me, a man who has told you the truth which I heard from Allah. Ibrahim didn’t do this.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JHN 8:41"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You do the works of your father.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They said to him, “We were not born of sexual immorality. We have one Father, Allah.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JHN 8:42"},"Therefore Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If Allah were your father, you would love me, for I came out and have come from Allah.\nFor I haven’t come of myself, but he sent me. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JHN 8:43"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Why don’t you understand my speech? Because you can’t hear my word.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JHN 8:44"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You are of your father, the Iblis, and you want to do the desires of your father. He was a murderer from the\nbeginning, and doesn’t stand in the truth, because there is no truth in him. When he speaks a lie, he speaks on his own; for he\nis a liar, and the father of lies. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"JHN 8:45"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But because I tell the truth, you don’t believe me. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"JHN 8:46"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Which of you convicts me of sin? If I tell the truth, why do you not believe me?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"JHN 8:47"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who is of Allah hears the words of Allah. For this cause you don’t hear, because you are not of\nAllah.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"JHN 8:48"},"Then the Jews answered him, “Don’t we say well that you are a Samaritan, and have a demon?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"JHN 8:49"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I don’t have a demon, but I honour my Father and you dishonour me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"JHN 8:50"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But I don’t seek my own glory. There is one who seeks and judges.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"JHN 8:51"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly, I tell you, if a person keeps my word, he will never see\ndeath.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"JHN 8:52"},"Then the Jews said to him, “Now we know that you have a demon. Ibrahim died, as did the prophets; and you say,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘If a man keeps my word, he will never taste of death.’"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"JHN 8:53"},"Are you greater than our father, Ibrahim, who died? The prophets died. Who do you make yourself out to be?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"JHN 8:54"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If I glorify myself, my glory is nothing. It is my Father who glorifies me, of whom you say that he is\nour Allah. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"JHN 8:55"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You have not known him, but I know him. If I said, ‘I don’t know him,’ I would be like you, a liar. But I know him\nand keep his word. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"JHN 8:56"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Your father Ibrahim rejoiced to see my day. He saw it, and was\nglad.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57","sid":"JHN 8:57"},"The Jews therefore said to him, “You are not yet fifty years old! Have you seen Ibrahim?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58","sid":"JHN 8:58"},"Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly, I tell you, before Ibrahim came into existence, I\nAM."]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["8:58 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 3:14"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59","sid":"JHN 8:59"},"Therefore they took up stones to throw at him, but Isa was hidden, and went out of the temple, having gone through the\nmiddle of them, and so passed by. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9","sid":"JHN 9"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 9:1"},"As he passed by, he saw a man blind from birth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 9:2"},"His disciples asked him, “Rabbi, who sinned, this man or his parents, that he was born blind?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 9:3"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“This man didn’t sin, nor did his parents; but, that the works of Allah might be revealed in him.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 9:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I must work the works of him who sent me while it is day. The night is coming, when no one can work.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 9:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["While I am in the world, I am the light of the world.”"]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 9:6"},"When he had said this, he spat on the ground, made mud with the saliva, anointed the blind man’s eyes with the mud,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 9:7"},"and said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Go, wash in the pool of Siloam”"]}," (which means “Sent”). So he went away, washed, and came back\nseeing. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 9:8"},"The neighbours therefore, and those who saw that he was blind before, said, “Isn’t this he who sat and begged?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 9:9"},"Others were saying, “It is he.” Still others were saying, “He looks like him.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “I am he.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 9:10"},"They therefore were asking him, “How were your eyes opened?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 9:11"},"He answered, “A man called Isa made mud, anointed my eyes, and said to me,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘Go to the pool of Siloam and wash.’"]}," So I went away and washed, and I received sight.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 9:12"},"Then they asked him, “Where is he?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “I don’t know.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 9:13"},"They brought him who had been blind to the Pharisees. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 9:14"},"It was a Sabbath when Isa made the mud and opened his eyes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 9:15"},"Again therefore the Pharisees also asked him how he received his sight. He said to them, “He put mud on my eyes, I\nwashed, and I see.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 9:16"},"Some therefore of the Pharisees said, “This man is not from Allah, because he doesn’t keep the Sabbath.” Others said,\n“How can a man who is a sinner do such signs?” There was division amongst them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 9:17"},"Therefore they asked the blind man again, “What do you say about him, because he opened your eyes?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “He is a prophet.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 9:18"},"The Jews therefore didn’t believe concerning him, that he had been blind, and had received his sight, until they called\nthe parents of him who had received his sight, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 9:19"},"and asked them, “Is this your son, whom you say was born blind? How then does he now see?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 9:20"},"His parents answered them, “We know that this is our son, and that he was born blind;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 9:21"},"but how he now sees, we don’t know; or who opened his eyes, we don’t know. He is of age. Ask him. He will speak for\nhimself.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 9:22"},"His parents said these things because they feared the Jews; for the Jews had already agreed that if any man would confess\nhim as Masih, he would be put out of the synagogue. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 9:23"},"Therefore his parents said, “He is of age. Ask him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 9:24"},"So they called the man who was blind a second time, and said to him, “Give glory to Allah. We know that this man is a\nsinner.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 9:25"},"He therefore answered, “I don’t know if he is a sinner. One thing I do know: that though I was blind, now I see.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 9:26"},"They said to him again, “What did he do to you? How did he open your eyes?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 9:27"},"He answered them, “I told you already, and you didn’t listen. Why do you want to hear it again? You don’t also want to\nbecome his disciples, do you?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 9:28"},"They insulted him and said, “You are his disciple, but we are disciples of Musa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 9:29"},"We know that Allah has spoken to Musa. But as for this man, we don’t know where he comes from.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 9:30"},"The man answered them, “How amazing! You don’t know where he comes from, yet he opened my eyes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 9:31"},"We know that Allah doesn’t listen to sinners, but if anyone is a worshipper of Allah, and does his will, he listens to\nhim.",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["9:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 66:18; Proverbs 15:29; 28:9"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 9:32"},"Since the world began it has never been heard of that anyone opened the eyes of someone born blind.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 9:33"},"If this man were not from Allah, he could do nothing.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 9:34"},"They answered him, “You were altogether born in sins, and do you teach us?” Then they threw him out.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 9:35"},"Isa heard that they had thrown him out, and finding him, he said,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Do you believe in the Son of Allah?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 9:36"},"He answered, “Who is he, Lord, that I may believe in him?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 9:37"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You have both seen him, and it is he who speaks with\nyou.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 9:38"},"He said, “Lord, I believe!” and he worshipped him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 9:39"},"Isa said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I came into this world for judgement, that those who don’t see may see; and that those who see may become\nblind.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 9:40"},"Those of the Pharisees who were with him heard these things, and said to him, “Are we also blind?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JHN 9:41"},"Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If you were blind, you would have no sin; but now you say, ‘We see.’ Therefore your sin\nremains."]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10","sid":"JHN 10"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 10:1"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly, I tell you, one who doesn’t enter by the door into the sheep fold, but climbs up some other way, is\na thief and a robber. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 10:2"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But one who enters in by the door is the shepherd of the sheep.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 10:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The gatekeeper opens the gate for him, and the sheep listen to his voice. He calls his own sheep by name, and leads\nthem out. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 10:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Whenever he brings out his own sheep, he goes before them, and the sheep follow him, for they know his voice.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 10:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They will by no means follow a stranger, but will flee from him; for they don’t know the voice of\nstrangers.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 10:6"},"Isa spoke this parable to them, but they didn’t understand what he was telling them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 10:7"},"Isa therefore said to them again, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly, I tell you, I am the sheep’s door.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 10:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["All who came before me are thieves and robbers, but the sheep didn’t listen to them.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 10:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am the door. If anyone enters in by me, he will be saved, and will go in and go out, and will find pasture.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 10:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The thief only comes to steal, kill, and destroy. I came that they may have life, and may have it abundantly.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 10:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am the good shepherd."]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah\n40:11; Ezekiel 34:11-12,15,22"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The good shepherd lays down his life for the sheep.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 10:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who is a hired hand, and not a shepherd, who doesn’t own the sheep, sees the wolf coming, leaves the sheep, and\nflees. The wolf snatches the sheep, and scatters them. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 10:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The hired hand flees because he is a hired hand, and doesn’t care for the sheep.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 10:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am the good shepherd. I know my own, and I’m known by my own;\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 10:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["even as the Father knows me, and I know the Father. I lay down my life for the sheep.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 10:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I have other sheep, which are not of this fold."]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 56:8 "]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I must bring them also, and they will hear my voice. They will become one flock with one\nshepherd. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 10:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Therefore the Father loves me, because I lay down my life,\n"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 53:7-8"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["that I may take it again.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 10:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["No one takes it away from me, but I lay it down by myself. I have power to lay it down, and I have power to take it\nagain. I received this commandment from my Father.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 10:19"},"Therefore a division arose again amongst the Jews because of these words.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 10:20"},"Many of them said, “He has a demon, and is insane! Why do you listen to him?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 10:21"},"Others said, “These are not the sayings of one possessed by a demon. It isn’t possible for a demon to open the eyes of\nthe blind, is it?”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 4:11"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 10:22"},"It was the Feast of the Dedication",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The “Feast of the Dedication” is the Greek name for “Hanukkah”, a\ncelebration of the rededication of the Temple."]}],"caller":"+"}," at Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 10:23"},"It was winter, and Isa was walking in the temple, in Sulaiman’s porch.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 10:24"},"The Jews therefore came around him and said to him, “How long will you hold us in suspense? If you are the Masih, tell us\nplainly.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 10:25"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I told you, and you don’t believe. The works that I do in my Father’s name, these testify about\nme. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 10:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But you don’t believe, because you are not of my sheep, as I told you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 10:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 10:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I give eternal life to them. They will never perish, and no one will snatch them out of my hand.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 10:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["My Father who has given them to me is greater than all. No one is able to snatch them out of my Father’s hand.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 10:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I and the Father are one.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 10:31"},"Therefore Jews took up stones again to stone him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 10:32"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I have shown you many good works from my Father. For which of those works do you stone\nme?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 10:33"},"The Jews answered him, “We don’t stone you for a good work, but for blasphemy: because you, being a man, make yourself\nAllah.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 10:34"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Isn’t it written in your law, ‘I said, you are\ngods?’"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:34 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 82:6"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 10:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If he called them gods, to whom the word of Allah came (and the Scripture can’t be broken),\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 10:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["do you say of him whom the Father sanctified and sent into the world, ‘You blaspheme,’ because I said, ‘I am the Son\nof Allah?’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 10:37"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If I don’t do the works of my Father, don’t believe me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 10:38"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But if I do them, though you don’t believe me, believe the works, that you may know and believe that the Father is\nin me, and I in the Father.” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 10:39"},"They sought again to seize him, and he went out of their hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 10:40"},"He went away again beyond the Jordan into the place where Yahya was baptising at first, and he stayed there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JHN 10:41"},"Many came to him. They said, “Yahya indeed did no sign, but everything that Yahya said about this man is true.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JHN 10:42"},"Many believed in him there. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11","sid":"JHN 11"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 11:1"},"Now a certain man was sick, Lazarus from Bethany, of the village of Maryam and her sister, Martha.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 11:2"},"It was that Maryam who had anointed the Lord with ointment and wiped his feet with her hair, whose brother, Lazarus, was\nsick. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 11:3"},"The sisters therefore sent to him, saying, “Lord, behold, he for whom you have great affection is sick.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 11:4"},"But when Isa heard it, he said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“This sickness is not to death, but for the glory of Allah, that Allah’s Son may be\nglorified by it.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 11:5"},"Now Isa loved Martha, and her sister, and Lazarus. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 11:6"},"When therefore he heard that he was sick, he stayed two days in the place where he was.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 11:7"},"Then after this he said to the disciples, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Let’s go into Judea\nagain.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 11:8"},"The disciples asked him, “Rabbi, the Jews were just trying to stone you. Are you going there again?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 11:9"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Aren’t there twelve hours of daylight? If a man walks in the day, he doesn’t stumble, because he sees\nthe light of this world. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 11:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But if a man walks in the night, he stumbles, because the light isn’t in\nhim.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 11:11"},"He said these things, and after that, he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Our friend, Lazarus, has fallen asleep, but I am going so\nthat I may awake him out of sleep.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 11:12"},"The disciples therefore said, “Lord, if he has fallen asleep, he will recover.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 11:13"},"Now Isa had spoken of his death, but they thought that he spoke of taking rest in sleep.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 11:14"},"So Isa said to them plainly then, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Lazarus is dead. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 11:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am glad for your sakes that I was not there, so that you may believe. Nevertheless, let’s go to\nhim.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 11:16"},"Tau’ma therefore, who is called Didymus,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Didymus” means\n“Twin”."]}],"caller":"+"}," said to his fellow disciples, “Let’s go also, that we may die with him.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 11:17"},"So when Isa came, he found that he had been in the tomb four days already.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 11:18"},"Now Bethany was near Jerusalem, about fifteen stadia",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:18\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["15 stadia is about 2.8 kilometres or 1.7 miles"]}],"caller":"+"}," away. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 11:19"},"Many of the Jews had joined the women around Martha and Maryam, to console them concerning their brother.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 11:20"},"Then when Martha heard that Isa was coming, she went and met him, but Maryam stayed in the house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 11:21"},"Therefore Martha said to Isa, “Lord, if you would have been here, my brother wouldn’t have died.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 11:22"},"Even now I know that whatever you ask of Allah, Allah will give you.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 11:23"},"Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Your brother will rise again.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 11:24"},"Martha said to him, “I know that he will rise again in the resurrection at the last day.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 11:25"},"Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am the resurrection and the life. He who believes in me will still live, even if he dies.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 11:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Whoever lives and believes in me will never die. Do you believe\nthis?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 11:27"},"She said to him, “Yes, Lord. I have come to believe that you are the Masih, Allah’s Son, he who comes into the world.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 11:28"},"When she had said this, she went away and called Maryam, her sister, secretly, saying, “The Teacher is here and is\ncalling you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 11:29"},"When she heard this, she arose quickly and went to him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 11:30"},"Now Isa had not yet come into the village, but was in the place where Martha met him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 11:31"},"Then the Jews who were with her in the house and were consoling her, when they saw Maryam, that she rose up quickly and\nwent out, followed her, saying, “She is going to the tomb to weep there.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 11:32"},"Therefore when Maryam came to where Isa was and saw him, she fell down at his feet, saying to him, “Lord, if you would\nhave been here, my brother wouldn’t have died.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 11:33"},"When Isa therefore saw her weeping, and the Jews weeping who came with her, he groaned in the spirit, and was troubled,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 11:34"},"and said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Where have you laid him?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They told him, “Lord, come and see.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 11:35"},"Isa wept. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 11:36"},"The Jews therefore said, “See how much affection he had for him!”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 11:37"},"Some of them said, “Couldn’t this man, who opened the eyes of him who was blind, have also kept this man from dying?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 11:38"},"Isa therefore, again groaning in himself, came to the tomb. Now it was a cave, and a stone lay against it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 11:39"},"Isa said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Take away the stone.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Martha, the sister of him who was dead, said to him, “Lord, by this time there is a stench, for he has been dead four days.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 11:40"},"Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Didn’t I tell you that if you believed, you would see Allah’s\nglory?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JHN 11:41"},"So they took away the stone from the place where the dead man was\nlying.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:41 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU omits “from the place where the dead man was\nlying.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," Isa lifted up his eyes, and said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Father, I thank you that you listened to me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JHN 11:42"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I know that you always listen to me, but because of the multitude standing around I said this, that they may believe\nthat you sent me.” "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JHN 11:43"},"When he had said this, he cried with a loud voice, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Lazarus, come\nout!”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JHN 11:44"},"He who was dead came out, bound hand and foot with wrappings, and his face was wrapped around with a cloth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Free him, and let him go.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"JHN 11:45"},"Therefore many of the Jews who came to Maryam and saw what Isa did believed in him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"JHN 11:46"},"But some of them went away to the Pharisees and told them the things which Isa had done.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"JHN 11:47"},"The chief priests therefore and the Pharisees gathered a council, and said, “What are we doing? For this man does many\nsigns. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"JHN 11:48"},"If we leave him alone like this, everyone will believe in him, and the Romans will come and take away both our place and\nour nation.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"JHN 11:49"},"But a certain one of them, Caiaphas, being high priest that year, said to them, “You know nothing at all,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"JHN 11:50"},"nor do you consider that it is advantageous for us that one man should die for the people, and that the whole nation not\nperish.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"JHN 11:51"},"Now he didn’t say this of himself, but being high priest that year, he prophesied that Isa would die for the nation,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"JHN 11:52"},"and not for the nation only, but that he might also gather together into one the children of Allah who are scattered\nabroad. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"JHN 11:53"},"So from that day forward they took counsel that they might put him to death.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"JHN 11:54"},"Isa therefore walked no more openly amongst the Jews, but departed from there into the country near the wilderness, to a\ncity called Ephraim. He stayed there with his disciples. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"JHN 11:55"},"Now the Passover of the Jews was at hand. Many went up from the country to Jerusalem before the Passover, to purify\nthemselves. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"JHN 11:56"},"Then they sought for Isa and spoke with one another as they stood in the temple, “What do you think—that he isn’t coming\nto the feast at all?” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57","sid":"JHN 11:57"},"Now the chief priests and the Pharisees had commanded that if anyone knew where he was, he should report it, that they\nmight seize him. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12","sid":"JHN 12"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 12:1"},"Then six days before the Passover, Isa came to Bethany, where Lazarus was, who had been dead, whom he raised from the\ndead. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 12:2"},"So they made him a supper there. Martha served, but Lazarus was one of those who sat at the table with him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 12:3"},"Therefore Maryam took a pound",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["a Roman pound of 12 ounces, or about 340\ngrams"]}],"caller":"+"}," of ointment of pure nard, very precious, and anointed Isa’ss feet and wiped his feet with her hair. The house was\nfilled with the fragrance of the ointment. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 12:4"},"Then Yehuda Iscariot, Shima’un’s son, one of his disciples, who would betray him, said,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 12:5"},"“Why wasn’t this ointment sold for three hundred denarii,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["300 denarii was about a year’s wages for an agricultural\nlabourer."]}],"caller":"+"}," and given to the poor?” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 12:6"},"Now he said this, not because he cared for the poor, but because he was a thief, and having the money box, used to steal\nwhat was put into it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 12:7"},"But Isa said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Leave her alone. She has kept this for the day of my burial.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 12:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For you always have the poor with you, but you don’t always have\nme.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 12:9"},"A large crowd therefore of the Jews learnt that he was there, and they came, not for Isa’s sake only, but that they might\nsee Lazarus also, whom he had raised from the dead. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 12:10"},"But the chief priests conspired to put Lazarus to death also,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 12:11"},"because on account of him many of the Jews went away and believed in Isa.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 12:12"},"On the next day a great multitude had come to the feast. When they heard that Isa was coming to Jerusalem,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 12:13"},"they took the branches of the palm trees and went out to meet him, and cried out,\n“Hosanna!",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Hosanna” means “save us” or “help us, we\npray”."]}],"caller":"+"}," Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord,",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:13\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 118:25-26 "]}],"caller":"+"}," the King of Israel!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 12:14"},"Isa, having found a young donkey, sat on it. As it is written,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 12:15"},"“Don’t be afraid, daughter of Zion. Behold, your King comes, sitting on a donkey’s\ncolt.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zakariya 9:9"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 12:16"},"His disciples didn’t understand these things at first, but when Isa was glorified, then they remembered that these things\nwere written about him, and that they had done these things to him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 12:17"},"The multitude therefore that was with him when he called Lazarus out of the tomb and raised him from the dead was\ntestifying about it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 12:18"},"For this cause also the multitude went and met him, because they heard that he had done this sign.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 12:19"},"The Pharisees therefore said amongst themselves, “See how you accomplish nothing. Behold, the world has gone after him.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 12:20"},"Now there were certain Greeks amongst those that went up to worship at the feast.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 12:21"},"These, therefore, came to Philip, who was from Bethsaida of Galilee, and asked him, saying, “Sir, we want to see Isa.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 12:22"},"Philip came and told Andreas, and in turn, Andreas came with Philip, and they told Isa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 12:23"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The time has come for the Son of Man to be glorified.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 12:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly I tell you, unless a grain of wheat falls into the earth and dies, it remains by itself alone. But if\nit dies, it bears much fruit. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 12:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who loves his life will lose it. He who hates his life in this world will keep it to eternal life.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 12:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If anyone serves me, let him follow me. Where I am, there my servant will also be. If anyone serves me, the Father\nwill honour him."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 12:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Now my soul is troubled. What shall I say? ‘Father, save me from this time?’ But I came to this time for this\ncause. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 12:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Father, glorify your name!”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then a voice came out of the sky, saying, “I have both glorified it, and will glorify it again.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 12:29"},"Therefore the multitude who stood by and heard it said that it had thundered. Others said, “An angel has spoken to him.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 12:30"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“This voice hasn’t come for my sake, but for your sakes.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 12:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Now is the judgement of this world. Now the prince of this world will be cast out.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 12:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["And I, if I am lifted up from the earth, will draw all people to\nmyself.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 12:33"},"But he said this, signifying by what kind of death he should die.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 12:34"},"The multitude answered him, “We have heard out of the law that the Masih remains\nforever.",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:34 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 9:7; Daniel 2:44; See Isaiah 53:8"]}],"caller":"+"}," How do you say,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘The Son of Man must be lifted up?’"]}," Who is this Son of Man?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 12:35"},"Isa therefore said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Yet a little while the light is with you. Walk while you have the light, that darkness\ndoesn’t overtake you. He who walks in the darkness doesn’t know where he is going.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 12:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["While you have the light, believe in the light, that you may become children of\nlight.”"]}," Isa said these things, and he departed and hid himself from them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 12:37"},"But though he had done so many signs before them, yet they didn’t believe in him,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 12:38"},"that the word of Isaiah the prophet might be fulfilled, which he spoke,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Lord, who has believed our report? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["To whom has the arm of the Lord been revealed?”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:38\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 53:1"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 12:39"},"For this cause they couldn’t believe, for Isaiah said again,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 12:40"},"“He has blinded their eyes and he hardened their heart, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["lest they should see with their eyes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and perceive with their heart, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and would turn, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I would heal them.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:40 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 6:10"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JHN 12:41"},"Isaiah said these things when he saw his glory, and spoke of him.\n",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:41 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 6:1"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JHN 12:42"},"Nevertheless even many of the rulers believed in him, but because of the Pharisees they didn’t confess it, so that they\nwouldn’t be put out of the synagogue, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"JHN 12:43"},"for they loved men’s praise more than Allah’s praise. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"JHN 12:44"},"Isa cried out and said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Whoever believes in me, believes not in me, but in him who sent me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"JHN 12:45"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who sees me sees him who sent me. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"JHN 12:46"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I have come as a light into the world, that whoever believes in me may not remain in the darkness.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"JHN 12:47"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If anyone listens to my sayings, and doesn’t believe, I don’t judge him. For I came not to judge the world, but to\nsave the world. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"JHN 12:48"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who rejects me, and doesn’t receive my sayings, has one who judges him. The word that I spoke will judge him in\nthe last day. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"JHN 12:49"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For I spoke not from myself, but the Father who sent me, he gave me a commandment, what I should say, and what I\nshould speak. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"JHN 12:50"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I know that his commandment is eternal life. The things therefore which I speak, even as the Father has said to me,\nso I speak.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13","sid":"JHN 13"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 13:1"},"Now before the feast of the Passover, Isa, knowing that his time had come that he would depart from this world to the\nFather, having loved his own who were in the world, he loved them to the end.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 13:2"},"During supper, the Iblis having already put into the heart of Yehuda Iscariot, Shima’un’s son, to betray him,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 13:3"},"Isa, knowing that the Father had given all things into his hands, and that he came from Allah, and was going to Allah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 13:4"},"arose from supper, and laid aside his outer garments. He took a towel and wrapped a towel around his waist.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 13:5"},"Then he poured water into the basin, and began to wash the disciples’ feet and to wipe them with the towel that was\nwrapped around him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 13:6"},"Then he came to Shima’un Peter. He said to him, “Lord, do you wash my feet?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 13:7"},"Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You don’t know what I am doing now, but you will understand\nlater.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 13:8"},"Peter said to him, “You will never wash my feet!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If I don’t wash you, you have no part with me.”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 13:9"},"Shima’un Peter said to him, “Lord, not my feet only, but also my hands and my head!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 13:10"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Someone who has bathed only needs to have his feet washed, but is completely clean. You are clean,\nbut not all of you.” "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 13:11"},"For he knew him who would betray him, therefore he said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You are not all\nclean.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 13:12"},"So when he had washed their feet, put his outer garment back on, and sat down again, he said to them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Do you know what I have done to you? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 13:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You call me, ‘Teacher’ and ‘Lord.’ You say so correctly, for so I am.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 13:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If I then, the Lord and the Teacher, have washed your feet, you also ought to wash one another’s feet.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 13:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For I have given you an example, that you should also do as I have done to you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 13:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly I tell you, a servant is not greater than his lord, neither is one who is sent greater than he who\nsent him. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 13:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you know these things, blessed are you if you do them.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 13:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I don’t speak concerning all of you. I know whom I have chosen. But that the Scripture may be fulfilled, ‘He who\neats bread with me has lifted up his heel against me.’"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["13:18\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 41:9"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 13:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["From now on, I tell you before it happens, that when it happens, you may believe that I am he.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 13:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly I tell you, he who receives whomever I send, receives me; and he who receives me, receives him who\nsent me.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 13:21"},"When Isa had said this, he was troubled in spirit, and testified,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly I tell you that one of you will betray me.”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 13:22"},"The disciples looked at one another, perplexed about whom he spoke.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 13:23"},"One of his disciples, whom Isa loved, was at the table, leaning against Isa’s breast.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 13:24"},"Shima’un Peter therefore beckoned to him, and said to him, “Tell us who it is of whom he speaks.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 13:25"},"He, leaning back, as he was, on Isa’s breast, asked him, “Lord, who is it?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 13:26"},"Isa therefore answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“It is he to whom I will give this piece of bread when I have dipped\nit.”"]}," So when he had dipped the piece of bread, he gave it to Yehuda, the son of Shima’un Iscariot.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 13:27"},"After the piece of bread, then Iblis entered into him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“What you do, do quickly.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 13:28"},"Now nobody at the table knew why he said this to him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 13:29"},"For some thought, because Yehuda had the money box, that Isa said to him, “Buy what things we need for the feast,” or\nthat he should give something to the poor. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 13:30"},"Therefore having received that morsel, he went out immediately. It was night.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 13:31"},"When he had gone out, Isa said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Now the Son of Man has been glorified, and Allah has been glorified in him.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 13:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If Allah has been glorified in him, Allah will also glorify him in himself, and he will glorify him immediately.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 13:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Little children, I will be with you a little while longer. You will seek me, and as I said to the Jews, ‘Where I am\ngoing, you can’t come,’ so now I tell you. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 13:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["A new commandment I give to you, that you love one another. Just as I have loved you, you also love one another.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 13:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["By this everyone will know that you are my disciples, if you have love for one\nanother.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 13:36"},"Shima’un Peter said to him, “Lord, where are you going?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Where I am going, you can’t follow now, but you will follow\nafterwards.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 13:37"},"Peter said to him, “Lord, why can’t I follow you now? I will lay down my life for you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 13:38"},"Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Will you lay down your life for me? Most certainly I tell you, the rooster won’t crow until you\nhave denied me three times."]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"14","sid":"JHN 14"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 14:1"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Don’t let your heart be troubled. Believe in Allah. Believe also in me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 14:2"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["In my Father’s house are many homes. If it weren’t so, I would have told you. I am going to prepare a place for you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 14:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again, and will receive you to myself; that where I am, you may be\nthere also. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 14:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You know where I go, and you know the way.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 14:5"},"Tau’ma said to him, “Lord, we don’t know where you are going. How can we know the way?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 14:6"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am the way, the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father, except through me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 14:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you had known me, you would have known my Father also. From now on, you know him, and have seen\nhim.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 14:8"},"Philip said to him, “Lord, show us the Father, and that will be enough for us.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 14:9"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Have I been with you such a long time, and do you not know me, Philip? He who has seen me has seen\nthe Father. How do you say, ‘Show us the Father?’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 14:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t you believe that I am in the Father, and the Father in me? The words that I tell you, I speak not from myself;\nbut the Father who lives in me does his works. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 14:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Believe me that I am in the Father, and the Father in me; or else believe me for the very works’ sake.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 14:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly I tell you, he who believes in me, the works that I do, he will do also; and he will do greater works\nthan these, because I am going to my Father. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 14:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Whatever you will ask in my name, I will do it, that the Father may be glorified in the Son.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 14:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you will ask anything in my name, I will do it. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 14:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you love me, keep my commandments. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 14:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I will pray to the Father, and he will give you another Counsellor,\n"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek παρακλητον: Counsellor, Helper, Intercessor, Advocate, and\nComforter."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["that he may be with you forever:"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 14:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["the Spirit of truth, whom the world can’t receive; for it doesn’t see him and doesn’t know him. You know him, for he\nlives with you, and will be in you. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 14:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I will not leave you orphans. I will come to you. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 14:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Yet a little while, and the world will see me no more; but you will see me. Because I live, you will live also.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 14:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["In that day you will know that I am in my Father, and you in me, and I in you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 14:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["One who has my commandments and keeps them, that person is one who loves me. One who loves me will be loved by my\nFather, and I will love him, and will reveal myself to him.”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 14:22"},"Yehuda (not Iscariot) said to him, “Lord, what has happened that you are about to reveal yourself to us, and not to the\nworld?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 14:23"},"Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If a man loves me, he will keep my word. My Father will love him, and we will come to him, and\nmake our home with him. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 14:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who doesn’t love me doesn’t keep my words. The word which you hear isn’t mine, but the Father’s who sent me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 14:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I have said these things to you while still living with you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 14:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But the Counsellor, the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my name, will teach you all things, and will\nremind you of all that I said to you. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 14:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Peace I leave with you. My peace I give to you; not as the world gives, I give to you. Don’t let your heart be\ntroubled, neither let it be fearful. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 14:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You heard how I told you, ‘I go away, and I come to you.’ If you loved me, you would have rejoiced, because I said\n‘I am going to my Father;’ for the Father is greater than I. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 14:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Now I have told you before it happens so that when it happens, you may believe.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 14:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I will no more speak much with you, for the prince of the world comes, and he has nothing in me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 14:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But that the world may know that I love the Father, and as the Father commanded me, even so I do. Arise, let’s go\nfrom here."]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"15","sid":"JHN 15"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 15:1"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am the true vine, and my Father is the farmer. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 15:2"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Every branch in me that doesn’t bear fruit, he takes away. Every branch that bears fruit, he prunes, that it may bear\nmore fruit. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 15:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You are already pruned clean because of the word which I have spoken to you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 15:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Remain in me, and I in you. As the branch can’t bear fruit by itself unless it remains in the vine, so neither can\nyou, unless you remain in me. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 15:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am the vine. You are the branches. He who remains in me and I in him bears much fruit, for apart from me you can do\nnothing. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 15:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If a man doesn’t remain in me, he is thrown out as a branch and is withered; and they gather them, throw them into\nthe fire, and they are burnt. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 15:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you remain in me, and my words remain in you, you will ask whatever you desire, and it will be done for\nyou."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 15:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“In this my Father is glorified, that you bear much fruit; and so you will be my disciples.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 15:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Even as the Father has loved me, I also have loved you. Remain in my love.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 15:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you keep my commandments, you will remain in my love; even as I have kept my Father’s commandments, and remain in\nhis love. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 15:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I have spoken these things to you, that my joy may remain in you, and that your joy may be made\nfull."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 15:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“This is my commandment, that you love one another, even as I have loved you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 15:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Greater love has no one than this, that someone lay down his life for his friends.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 15:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You are my friends, if you do whatever I command you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 15:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["No longer do I call you servants, for the servant doesn’t know what his lord does. But I have called you friends,\nfor everything that I heard from my Father, I have made known to you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 15:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You didn’t choose me, but I chose you and appointed you, that you should go and bear fruit, and that your fruit\nshould remain; that whatever you will ask of the Father in my name, he may give it to\nyou."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 15:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I command these things to you, that you may love one another.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 15:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If the world hates you, you know that it has hated me before it hated you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 15:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you were of the world, the world would love its own. But because you are not of the world, since I chose you out\nof the world, therefore the world hates you. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 15:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Remember the word that I said to you: ‘A servant is not greater than his\nlord.’"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["15:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Yuhanna 13:16"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If they persecuted me, they will also persecute you. If they kept my word,\nthey will also keep yours. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 15:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But they will do all these things to you for my name’s sake, because they don’t know him who sent me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 15:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If I had not come and spoken to them, they would not have had sin; but now they have no excuse for their sin.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 15:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who hates me, hates my Father also. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 15:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If I hadn’t done amongst them the works which no one else did, they wouldn’t have had sin. But now they have seen\nand also hated both me and my Father. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 15:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But this happened so that the word may be fulfilled which was written in their law, ‘They hated me without a\ncause.’"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["15:25 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 35:19; 69:4"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 15:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“When the Counsellor"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek Parakletos: Counsellor, Helper, Advocate, Intercessor, and\nComforter."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["has come, whom I will send to you from the Father, the Spirit of truth, who proceeds from the Father, he will\ntestify about me. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 15:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You will also testify, because you have been with me from the\nbeginning."]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"16","sid":"JHN 16"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 16:1"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I have said these things to you so that you wouldn’t be caused to stumble.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 16:2"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They will put you out of the synagogues. Yes, the time comes that whoever kills you will think that he offers service\nto Allah. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 16:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They will do these things"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “to\nyou”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["because they have not known the Father, nor me. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 16:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But I have told you these things, so that when the time comes, you may remember that I told you about them. I didn’t\ntell you these things from the beginning, because I was with you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 16:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But now I am going to him who sent me, and none of you asks me, ‘Where are you going?’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 16:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But because I have told you these things, sorrow has filled your heart.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 16:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Nevertheless I tell you the truth: It is to your advantage that I go away, for if I don’t go away, the Counsellor\nwon’t come to you. But if I go, I will send him to you. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 16:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When he has come, he will convict the world about sin, about righteousness, and about judgement;\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 16:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["about sin, because they don’t believe in me; "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 16:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["about righteousness, because I am going to my Father, and you won’t see me any more;\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 16:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["about judgement, because the prince of this world has been judged.\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 16:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I still have many things to tell you, but you can’t bear them now.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 16:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["However when he, the Spirit of truth, has come, he will guide you into all truth, for he will not speak from\nhimself; but whatever he hears, he will speak. He will declare to you things that are coming.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 16:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He will glorify me, for he will take from what is mine, and will declare it to you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 16:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["All things that the Father has are mine; therefore I said that he\ntakes"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “will take” instead of “takes”"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["of mine and will declare it to you. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 16:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["A little while, and you will not see me. Again a little while, and you will see\nme.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 16:17"},"Some of his disciples therefore said to one another, “What is this that he says to us,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘A little while, and you won’t see me, and again a little while, and you will see\nme;’"]}," and, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘Because I go to the Father’"]},"?” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 16:18"},"They said therefore, “What is this that he says, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘A little\nwhile’"]},"? We don’t know what he is saying.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 16:19"},"Therefore Isa perceived that they wanted to ask him, and he said to them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Do you enquire amongst yourselves concerning this, that I said, ‘A little while, and you won’t see me, and again a little\nwhile, and you will see me?’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 16:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly I tell you that you will weep and lament, but the world will rejoice. You will be sorrowful, but your\nsorrow will be turned into joy. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 16:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["A woman, when she gives birth, has sorrow because her time has come. But when she has delivered the child, she\ndoesn’t remember the anguish any more, for the joy that a human being is born into the world.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 16:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Therefore you now have sorrow, but I will see you again, and your heart will rejoice, and no one will take your joy\naway from you."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 16:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“In that day you will ask me no questions. Most certainly I tell you, whatever you may ask of the Father in my name,\nhe will give it to you. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 16:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Until now, you have asked nothing in my name. Ask, and you will receive, that your joy may be made full.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 16:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I have spoken these things to you in figures of speech. But the time is coming when I will no more speak to you in\nfigures of speech, but will tell you plainly about the Father. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 16:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["In that day you will ask in my name; and I don’t say to you that I will pray to the Father for you,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 16:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for the Father himself loves you, because you have loved me, and have believed that I came from Allah.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 16:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I came from the Father, and have come into the world. Again, I leave the world, and go to the\nFather.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 16:29"},"His disciples said to him, “Behold, now you are speaking plainly, and using no figures of speech.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 16:30"},"Now we know that you know all things, and don’t need for anyone to question you. By this we believe that you came from\nAllah.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 16:31"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Do you now believe? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 16:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Behold, the time is coming, yes, and has now come, that you will be scattered, everyone to his own place, and you\nwill leave me alone. Yet I am not alone, because the Father is with me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 16:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I have told you these things, that in me you may have peace. In the world you have trouble; but cheer up! I have\novercome the world.” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"17","sid":"JHN 17"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 17:1"},"Isa said these things, then lifting up his eyes to heaven, he said,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Father, the time has come. Glorify your Son, that your Son may also glorify you;\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 17:2"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["even as you gave him authority over all flesh, so he will give eternal life to all whom you have given him.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 17:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["This is eternal life, that they should know you, the only true Allah, and him whom you sent, Al Masih Isa.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 17:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I glorified you on the earth. I have accomplished the work which you have given me to do.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 17:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Now, Father, glorify me with your own self with the glory which I had with you before the world existed.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 17:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I revealed your name to the people whom you have given me out of the world. They were yours, and you have given them\nto me. They have kept your word. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 17:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Now they have known that all things whatever you have given me are from you,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 17:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for the words which you have given me I have given to them, and they received them, and knew for sure that I came\nfrom you. They have believed that you sent me. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 17:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I pray for them. I don’t pray for the world, but for those whom you have given me, for they are yours.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 17:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["All things that are mine are yours, and yours are mine, and I am glorified in them.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 17:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am no more in the world, but these are in the world, and I am coming to you. Holy Father, keep them through your\nname which you have given me, that they may be one, even as we are.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 17:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["While I was with them in the world, I kept them in your name. I have kept those whom you have given me. None of them\nis lost except the son of destruction, that the Scripture might be fulfilled.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 17:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But now I come to you, and I say these things in the world, that they may have my joy made full in themselves.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 17:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I have given them your word. The world hated them, because they are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 17:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I pray not that you would take them from the world, but that you would keep them from the evil one.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 17:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They are not of the world even as I am not of the world.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 17:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Sanctify them in your truth. Your word is truth."]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["17:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 119:142"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 17:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["As you sent me into the world, even so I have sent them into the world.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 17:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For their sakes I sanctify myself, that they themselves also may be sanctified in truth.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 17:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Not for these only do I pray, but for those also who will believe in me through their word,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 17:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["that they may all be one; even as you, Father, are in me, and I in you, that they also may be one in us; that the\nworld may believe that you sent me. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 17:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The glory which you have given me, I have given to them; that they may be one, even as we are one;\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 17:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I in them, and you in me, that they may be perfected into one; that the world may know that you sent me and loved\nthem, even as you loved me. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 17:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Father, I desire that they also whom you have given me be with me where I am, that they may see my glory, which you\nhave given me, for you loved me before the foundation of the world.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 17:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Righteous Father, the world hasn’t known you, but I knew you; and these knew that you sent me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 17:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I made known to them your name, and will make it known; that the love with which you loved me may be in them, and I\nin them.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"18","sid":"JHN 18"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 18:1"},"When Isa had spoken these words, he went out with his disciples over the brook Kidron, where there was a garden, into\nwhich he and his disciples entered. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 18:2"},"Now Yehuda, who betrayed him, also knew the place, for Isa often met there with his disciples.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 18:3"},"Yehuda then, having taken a detachment of soldiers and officers from the chief priests and the Pharisees, came there with\nlanterns, torches, and weapons. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 18:4"},"Isa therefore, knowing all the things that were happening to him, went out, and said to them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Who are you looking for?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 18:5"},"They answered him, “Isa of Nazareth.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am he.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Yehuda also, who betrayed him, was standing with them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 18:6"},"When therefore he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am he,”"]}," they went backward, and fell to the ground.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 18:7"},"Again therefore he asked them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Who are you looking for?”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They said, “Isa of Nazareth.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 18:8"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I told you that I am he. If therefore you seek me, let these go their\nway,”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 18:9"},"that the word might be fulfilled which he spoke, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Of those whom you have given me, I have lost\nnone.”"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["18:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Yuhanna 6:39"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 18:10"},"Shima’un Peter therefore, having a sword, drew it, struck the high priest’s servant, and cut off his right ear. The\nservant’s name was Malchus. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 18:11"},"Isa therefore said to Peter, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Put the sword into its sheath. The cup which the Father has given me, shall I not\nsurely drink it?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 18:12"},"So the detachment, the commanding officer, and the officers of the Jews seized Isa and bound him,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 18:13"},"and led him to Annas first, for he was father-in-law to Caiaphas, who was high priest that year.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 18:14"},"Now it was Caiaphas who advised the Jews that it was expedient that one man should perish for the people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 18:15"},"Shima’un Peter followed Isa, as did another disciple. Now that disciple was known to the high priest, and entered in with\nIsa into the court of the high priest; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 18:16"},"but Peter was standing at the door outside. So the other disciple, who was known to the high priest, went out and spoke\nto her who kept the door, and brought in Peter. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 18:17"},"Then the maid who kept the door said to Peter, “Are you also one of this man’s disciples?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “I am not.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 18:18"},"Now the servants and the officers were standing there, having made a fire of coals, for it was cold. They were warming\nthemselves. Peter was with them, standing and warming himself. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 18:19"},"The high priest therefore asked Isa about his disciples and about his teaching.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 18:20"},"Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I spoke openly to the world. I always taught in synagogues, and in the temple, where the Jews\nalways meet. I said nothing in secret. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 18:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Why do you ask me? Ask those who have heard me what I said to them. Behold, they know the things which I\nsaid.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 18:22"},"When he had said this, one of the officers standing by slapped Isa with his hand, saying, “Do you answer the high priest\nlike that?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 18:23"},"Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If I have spoken evil, testify of the evil; but if well, why do you beat\nme?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 18:24"},"Annas sent him bound to Caiaphas, the high priest. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 18:25"},"Now Shima’un Peter was standing and warming himself. They said therefore to him, “You aren’t also one of his disciples,\nare you?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He denied it and said, “I am not.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 18:26"},"One of the servants of the high priest, being a relative of him whose ear Peter had cut off, said, “Didn’t I see you in\nthe garden with him?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 18:27"},"Peter therefore denied it again, and immediately the rooster crowed.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 18:28"},"They led Isa therefore from Caiaphas into the Praetorium. It was early, and they themselves didn’t enter into the\nPraetorium, that they might not be defiled, but might eat the Passover.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 18:29"},"Pilate therefore went out to them, and said, “What accusation do you bring against this man?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 18:30"},"They answered him, “If this man weren’t an evildoer, we wouldn’t have delivered him up to you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 18:31"},"Pilate therefore said to them, “Take him yourselves, and judge him according to your law.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Therefore the Jews said to him, “It is illegal for us to put anyone to death,”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 18:32"},"that the word of Isa might be fulfilled, which he spoke, signifying by what kind of death he should die.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 18:33"},"Pilate therefore entered again into the Praetorium, called Isa, and said to him, “Are you the King of the Jews?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 18:34"},"Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Do you say this by yourself, or did others tell you about\nme?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 18:35"},"Pilate answered, “I’m not a Jew, am I? Your own nation and the chief priests delivered you to me. What have you done?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 18:36"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“My Kingdom is not of this world. If my Kingdom were of this world, then my servants would fight, that\nI wouldn’t be delivered to the Jews. But now my Kingdom is not from\nhere.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 18:37"},"Pilate therefore said to him, “Are you a king then?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You say that I am a king. For this reason I have been born, and for this reason I have come into the\nworld, that I should testify to the truth. Everyone who is of the truth listens to my\nvoice.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 18:38"},"Pilate said to him, “What is truth?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When he had said this, he went out again to the Jews, and said to them, “I find no basis for a charge against him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 18:39"},"But you have a custom, that I should release someone to you at the Passover. Therefore, do you want me to release to you\nthe King of the Jews?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 18:40"},"Then they all shouted again, saying, “Not this man, but Barabbas!” Now Barabbas was a robber.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"19","sid":"JHN 19"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 19:1"},"So Pilate then took Isa, and flogged him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 19:2"},"The soldiers twisted thorns into a crown, and put it on his head, and dressed him in a purple garment.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 19:3"},"They kept saying, “Hail, King of the Jews!” and they kept slapping him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 19:4"},"Then Pilate went out again, and said to them, “Behold, I bring him out to you, that you may know that I find no basis for\na charge against him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 19:5"},"Isa therefore came out, wearing the crown of thorns and the purple garment. Pilate said to them, “Behold, the man!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 19:6"},"When therefore the chief priests and the officers saw him, they shouted, saying, “Crucify! Crucify!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Pilate said to them, “Take him yourselves, and crucify him, for I find no basis for a charge against him.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 19:7"},"The Jews answered him, “We have a law, and by our law he ought to die, because he made himself the Son of Allah.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 19:8"},"When therefore Pilate heard this saying, he was more afraid.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 19:9"},"He entered into the Praetorium again, and said to Isa, “Where are you from?” But Isa gave him no answer.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 19:10"},"Pilate therefore said to him, “Aren’t you speaking to me? Don’t you know that I have power to release you and have power\nto crucify you?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 19:11"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You would have no power at all against me, unless it were given to you from above. Therefore he who\ndelivered me to you has greater sin.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 19:12"},"At this, Pilate was seeking to release him, but the Jews cried out, saying, “If you release this man, you aren’t Caesar’s\nfriend! Everyone who makes himself a king speaks against Caesar!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 19:13"},"When Pilate therefore heard these words, he brought Isa out and sat down on the judgement seat at a place called “The\nPavement”, but in Hebrew, “Gabbatha.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 19:14"},"Now it was the Preparation Day of the Passover, at about the sixth\nhour.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“the sixth hour” would have been 6:00 a.m. according to the Roman timekeeping system, or noon for the\nJewish timekeeping system in use, then. "]}],"caller":"+"}," He said to the Jews, “Behold, your King!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 19:15"},"They cried out, “Away with him! Away with him! Crucify him!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Pilate said to them, “Shall I crucify your King?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The chief priests answered, “We have no king but Caesar!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 19:16"},"So then he delivered him to them to be crucified. So they took Isa and led him away.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 19:17"},"He went out, bearing his cross, to the place called “The Place of a Skull”, which is called in Hebrew, “Golgotha”,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 19:18"},"where they crucified him, and with him two others, on either side one, and Isa in the middle.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 19:19"},"Pilate wrote a title also, and put it on the cross. There was written, “JESUS OF NAZARETH, THE KING OF THE JEWS.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 19:20"},"Therefore many of the Jews read this title, for the place where Isa was crucified was near the city; and it was written\nin Hebrew, in Latin, and in Greek. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 19:21"},"The chief priests of the Jews therefore said to Pilate, “Don’t write, ‘The King of the Jews,’ but, ‘he said, “I am King\nof the Jews.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 19:22"},"Pilate answered, “What I have written, I have written.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 19:23"},"Then the soldiers, when they had crucified Isa, took his garments and made four parts, to every soldier a part; and also\nthe coat. Now the coat was without seam, woven from the top throughout.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 19:24"},"Then they said to one another, “Let’s not tear it, but cast lots for it to decide whose it will be,” that the Scripture\nmight be fulfilled, which says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“They parted my garments amongst them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For my cloak they cast lots.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["19:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 22:18"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Therefore the soldiers did these things. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 19:25"},"But standing by Isa’s cross were his mother, his mother’s sister, Maryam the wife of Clopas, and Maryam Magdalene.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 19:26"},"Therefore when Isa saw his mother, and the disciple whom he loved standing there, he said to his mother,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Woman, behold, your son!” "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 19:27"},"Then he said to the disciple, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Behold, your mother!”"]}," From that hour, the disciple took her to his own home.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 19:28"},"After this, Isa, seeing",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:28 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU, TR read “knowing” instead of “seeing”\n"]}],"caller":"+"}," that all things were now finished, that the Scripture might be fulfilled, said,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I am thirsty.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 19:29"},"Now a vessel full of vinegar was set there; so they put a sponge full of the vinegar on hyssop, and held it at his mouth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 19:30"},"When Isa therefore had received the vinegar, he said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“It is\nfinished.”"]}," He bowed his head, and gave up his spirit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 19:31"},"Therefore the Jews, because it was the Preparation Day, so that the bodies wouldn’t remain on the cross on the Sabbath\n(for that Sabbath was a special one), asked of Pilate that their legs might be broken, and that they might be taken away.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"JHN 19:32"},"Therefore the soldiers came, and broke the legs of the first, and of the other who was crucified with him;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"JHN 19:33"},"but when they came to Isa, and saw that he was already dead, they didn’t break his legs.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"JHN 19:34"},"However one of the soldiers pierced his side with a spear, and immediately blood and water came out.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"JHN 19:35"},"He who has seen has testified, and his testimony is true. He knows that he tells the truth, that you may believe.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"JHN 19:36"},"For these things happened that the Scripture might be fulfilled, “A bone of him will not be\nbroken.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["19:36 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 12:46; Numbers 9:12; Zabur 34:20\n"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"JHN 19:37"},"Again another Scripture says, “They will look on him whom they\npierced.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["19:37 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zakariya 12:10"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"JHN 19:38"},"After these things, Yusuf of Arimathaea, being a disciple of Isa, but secretly for fear of the Jews, asked of Pilate that\nhe might take away Isa’s body. Pilate gave him permission. He came therefore and took away his body.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"JHN 19:39"},"Nicodemus, who at first came to Isa by night, also came bringing a mixture of myrrh and aloes, about a hundred Roman\npounds.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:39 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["100 Roman pounds of 12 ounces each, or about 72 pounds, or 33\nKilograms."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"JHN 19:40"},"So they took Isa’s body, and bound it in linen cloths with the spices, as the custom of the Jews is to bury.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"JHN 19:41"},"Now in the place where he was crucified there was a garden. In the garden was a new tomb in which no man had ever yet\nbeen laid. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"JHN 19:42"},"Then because of the Jews’ Preparation Day (for the tomb was near at hand) they laid Isa there.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"20","sid":"JHN 20"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 20:1"},"Now on the first day of the week, Maryam Magdalene went early, while it was still dark, to the tomb, and saw the stone\ntaken away from the tomb. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 20:2"},"Therefore she ran and came to Shima’un Peter and to the other disciple whom Isa loved, and said to them, “They have taken\naway the Lord out of the tomb, and we don’t know where they have laid him!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 20:3"},"Therefore Peter and the other disciple went out, and they went towards the tomb.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 20:4"},"They both ran together. The other disciple outran Peter, and came to the tomb first.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 20:5"},"Stooping and looking in, he saw the linen cloths lying, yet he didn’t enter in.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 20:6"},"Then Shima’un Peter came, following him, and entered into the tomb. He saw the linen cloths lying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 20:7"},"and the cloth that had been on his head, not lying with the linen cloths, but rolled up in a place by itself.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 20:8"},"So then the other disciple who came first to the tomb also entered in, and he saw and believed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 20:9"},"For as yet they didn’t know the Scripture, that he must rise from the dead.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 20:10"},"So the disciples went away again to their own homes. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 20:11"},"But Maryam was standing outside at the tomb weeping. So as she wept, she stooped and looked into the tomb,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 20:12"},"and she saw two angels in white sitting, one at the head, and one at the feet, where the body of Isa had lain.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 20:13"},"They asked her, “Woman, why are you weeping?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["She said to them, “Because they have taken away my Lord, and I don’t know where they have laid him.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 20:14"},"When she had said this, she turned around and saw Isa standing, and didn’t know that it was Isa.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 20:15"},"Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Woman, why are you weeping? Who are you looking\nfor?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["She, supposing him to be the gardener, said to him, “Sir, if you have carried him away, tell me where you have laid him, and\nI will take him away.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 20:16"},"Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Maryam.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["She turned and said to him, “Rabboni!”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Rabboni is a transliteration of the Hebrew word for “great\nteacher.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," which is to say, “Teacher!”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, Master"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 20:17"},"Isa said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Don’t hold me, for I haven’t yet ascended to my Father; but go to my brothers and tell them, ‘I am\nascending to my Father and your Father, to my Allah and your Allah.’”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 20:18"},"Maryam Magdalene came and told the disciples that she had seen the Lord, and that he had said these things to her.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 20:19"},"When therefore it was evening on that day, the first day of the week, and when the doors were locked where the disciples\nwere assembled, for fear of the Jews, Isa came and stood in the middle, and said to them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Peace be to you.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 20:20"},"When he had said this, he showed them his hands and his side. The disciples therefore were glad when they saw the Lord.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 20:21"},"Isa therefore said to them again, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Peace be to you. As the Father has sent me, even so I send\nyou.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 20:22"},"When he had said this, he breathed on them, and said to them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Receive the Holy Spirit! "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 20:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you forgive anyone’s sins, they have been forgiven them. If you retain anyone’s sins, they have been\nretained.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 20:24"},"But Tau’ma, one of the twelve, called Didymus, wasn’t with them when Isa came.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 20:25"},"The other disciples therefore said to him, “We have seen the Lord!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But he said to them, “Unless I see in his hands the print of the nails, put my finger into the print of the nails, and put\nmy hand into his side, I will not believe.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"JHN 20:26"},"After eight days again his disciples were inside and Tau’ma was with them. Isa came, the doors being locked, and stood in\nthe middle, and said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Peace be to you.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"JHN 20:27"},"Then he said to Tau’ma, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Reach here your finger, and see my hands. Reach here your hand, and put it into my side.\nDon’t be unbelieving, but believing.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"JHN 20:28"},"Tau’ma answered him, “My Lord and my Allah!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"JHN 20:29"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Because you have seen me,"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:29\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “Tau’ma,”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["you have believed. Blessed are those who have not seen, and have\nbelieved.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"JHN 20:30"},"Therefore Isa did many other signs in the presence of his disciples, which are not written in this book;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"JHN 20:31"},"but these are written, that you may believe that Isa is the Masih, the Son of Allah, and that believing you may have life\nin his name. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"21","sid":"JHN 21"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"JHN 21:1"},"After these things, Isa revealed himself again to the disciples at the sea of Tiberias. He revealed himself this way.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"JHN 21:2"},"Shima’un Peter, Tau’ma called Didymus, Nathanael of Cana in Galilee, and the sons of Zebedee, and two others of his\ndisciples were together. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"JHN 21:3"},"Shima’un Peter said to them, “I’m going fishing.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They told him, “We are also coming with you.” They immediately went out, and entered into the boat. That night, they caught\nnothing. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"JHN 21:4"},"But when day had already come, Isa stood on the beach, yet the disciples didn’t know that it was Isa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"JHN 21:5"},"Isa therefore said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Children, have you anything to eat?”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They answered him, “No.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"JHN 21:6"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Cast the net on the right side of the boat, and you will find\nsome.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They cast it therefore, and now they weren’t able to draw it in for the multitude of fish.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"JHN 21:7"},"That disciple therefore whom Isa loved said to Peter, “It’s the Lord!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So when Shima’un Peter heard that it was the Lord, he wrapped his coat around himself (for he was naked), and threw himself\ninto the sea. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"JHN 21:8"},"But the other disciples came in the little boat (for they were not far from the land, but about two hundred\ncubits",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["200 cubits is about 100 yards or about 91\nmetres"]}],"caller":"+"}," away), dragging the net full of fish. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"JHN 21:9"},"So when they got out on the land, they saw a fire of coals there, with fish and bread laid on it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"JHN 21:10"},"Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Bring some of the fish which you have just\ncaught.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"JHN 21:11"},"Shima’un Peter went up, and drew the net to land, full of one hundred and fifty-three great fish. Even though there were\nso many, the net wasn’t torn. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"JHN 21:12"},"Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Come and eat breakfast!”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["None of the disciples dared enquire of him, “Who are you?” knowing that it was the Lord.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"JHN 21:13"},"Then Isa came and took the bread, gave it to them, and the fish likewise.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"JHN 21:14"},"This is now the third time that Isa was revealed to his disciples after he had risen from the dead.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"JHN 21:15"},"So when they had eaten their breakfast, Isa said to Shima’un Peter,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Shima’un, son of Yunus, do you love me more than these?”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to him, “Yes, Lord; you know that I have affection for you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Feed my lambs.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"JHN 21:16"},"He said to him again a second time, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Shima’un, son of Yunus, do you love\nme?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to him, “Yes, Lord; you know that I have affection for you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Tend my sheep.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"JHN 21:17"},"He said to him the third time, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Shima’un, son of Yunus, do you have affection for\nme?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Peter was grieved because he asked him the third time, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Do you have affection for\nme?”"]}," He said to him, “Lord, you know everything. You know that I have affection for you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Feed my sheep. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"JHN 21:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly I tell you, when you were young, you dressed yourself and walked where you wanted to. But when you\nare old, you will stretch out your hands, and another will dress you and carry you where you don’t want to\ngo.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"JHN 21:19"},"Now he said this, signifying by what kind of death he would glorify Allah. When he had said this, he said to him,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Follow me.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"JHN 21:20"},"Then Peter, turning around, saw a disciple following. This was the disciple whom Isa loved, the one who had also leaned\non Isa’s breast at the supper and asked, “Lord, who is going to betray you?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"JHN 21:21"},"Peter seeing him, said to Isa, “Lord, what about this man?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"JHN 21:22"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If I desire that he stay until I come, what is that to you? You follow\nme.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"JHN 21:23"},"This saying therefore went out amongst the brothers,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:23\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word for “brothers” here may be also correctly translated “brothers and sisters” or\n“siblings.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," that this disciple wouldn’t die. Yet Isa didn’t say to him that he wouldn’t die, but,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If I desire that he stay until I come, what is that to you?”"]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"JHN 21:24"},"This is the disciple who testifies about these things, and wrote these things. We know that his witness is true.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"JHN 21:25"},"There are also many other things which Isa did, which if they would all be written, I suppose that even the world itself\nwouldn’t have room for the books that would be written. "]}]}